<EmprzAnastazia@a...> wrote:
> 
> > "It's just a matter of getting a vehicle form built in, like I 
> did," 
> > Empath points out.  "Granted, we can't achieve supersonic speeds 
> > anymore, but it's worth it.  Any tech-bot could do you that 
favor - 
> > knowing our resident genius, Wheeljack-X, he'd be happy to 
help."  
> > 
> > A whispering voice causes her ears to prick up, despite knowing 
> that 
> > there was nobody to make the sound - it's not coming through the 
> air, 
> > but rather in her mind.  Empath blinks.  "Did you hear something?"
> 
> Cocking a brow. "No, I didn't," she glanced about her. She was 
uneasy 
> enough as it was, & now Empath had to make her even more uneasy. 
> 
> Wheeljack-X, huh? she thought. Seemed that if he would become 
> involved that something may go wrong. But then again, if he was 
like 
> the Wheeljack she 'knew', then he was a genius is some form. But 
> would he even attempt to return her to her former form?
> 
> She moved a couple paces from Empath. "Thank you. It seems I still 
> have a lot to do." 
> 
> With that, she padded away from Empath. Walking past Windlord, not 
> stopping. "I ask at least that no one follows me, won't attract as 
> much attention if I am unaccompanied by some form of .. Autobot." 
she 
> growled as she padded by him & then broke out into a run.

"Good luck, old friend," Empath says softly, knowing Maxima won't 
hear her.  The femme heads back to the others.  "Let her go.  She 
won't cause any trouble."
